snippet: The elections were seen as a test of an accord brokered by the European Union that aimed to overcome ethnic enmities in Kosovo and the region.
abstract: Future of a landmark power-sharing agreement between Serbs and ethnic Albanians in Kosovo is called into doubt after local elections in Kosovo are blighted by violence and intimidation by people suspected of being Serbian hard-liners.
lead_paragraph: The elections were seen as a test of an accord brokered by the European Union that aimed to overcome ethnic enmities in Kosovo and the region.

headline.print_headline:
Accord Tested
Amid Violence
In Kosovo Vote
